for people who live here

01:11.416 --> 01:13.750
or are married to people who live here,

01:13.833 --> 01:15.541
which disqualifies <i>you!</i>

01:15.625 --> 01:18.416
Ha-ha! Okay. Nice to see you too, Di.

01:18.500 --> 01:19.541
Hi, Uncle Kurt!

01:19.625 --> 01:20.916
<i>Ex</i>-uncle.

01:21.000 --> 01:22.416
I'm just here to get my grill.

01:22.500 --> 01:25.125
Heidi's hosting
her bird book club next week.

01:25.208 --> 01:27.625
They're reading <i>The Pelican Brief. </i>Again.

01:27.708 --> 01:29.333
You're still dating that ditzy--

01:29.416 --> 01:31.625
Heidi! How are ya, hon?

01:31.708 --> 01:33.291
Hi, Diane. Hi, Daniel.

01:33.875 --> 01:34.708
-Ah!

01:34.791 --> 01:37.416
Goddammit! I need to let that cool down.

01:37.500 --> 01:40.250
-Kurt, the birds are in the car.
-Ten-four, babe.

01:40.333 --> 01:41.750
Ouch, ouch, ouch, ouch!

01:41.833 --> 01:44.000
All right, have a good Opening Day. Bye!

01:44.083 --> 01:46.833
-Kinda hard now with no hot meat!
-Uh! Tss! Ah!

01:46.916 --> 01:49.916
Hey, we don't need food and warmth
to have a good time.

01:50.000 --> 01:52.958
When I say "grounds,"
you say "crew!" Grounds!

01:53.041 --> 01:53.875
Cold!

01:53.958 --> 01:56.083
Oh, yeah, my nips are rock hard.

01:56.166 --> 01:57.791
And not in the fun way.

01:57.875 --> 01:59.375
Isn't it great, Daniel?

01:59.458 --> 02:02.333
We get to do this together
all season long!

02:02.416 --> 02:03.625
Ugh!

02:03.708 --> 02:06.041
Let's go, Cubbies!

02:15.875 --> 02:18.041
Another perfect rooftop party.

02:18.125 --> 02:20.333
It's endearing
you considered that a party.

02:20.416 --> 02:22.333
Oh, we left the cooler in the hallway.

02:22.416 --> 02:25.041
Oh, I'll get it. I forgot my flip flops.

02:26.458 --> 02:27.458
Hey!

02:27.541 --> 02:29.583
Oh, sorry, thought this was hallway beer.

02:29.666 --> 02:32.541
No, <i>that's</i> hallway beer.

02:32.625 --> 02:35.000
Okay, that fucking rocks!

02:35.083 --> 02:36.166
What did you just say?

02:36.250 --> 02:37.958
I said, "That fucking rocks."

02:38.041 --> 02:40.541
I thought I was the only one
who said that.

02:40.625 --> 02:42.416
That fucking rocks!

02:42.500 --> 02:44.166
I'm Diane, by the way.

02:44.250 --> 02:46.333
Amanda. I'm moving in down the hall,

02:46.416 --> 02:49.250
but I needed to take a White Claw break.
Want to join me?

02:49.333 --> 02:51.375
Does a bear shit in the woods?

02:51.458 --> 02:54.083
No, they do it at Soldier Field, baby.

02:59.541 --> 03:00.583
Claws out!

03:06.375 --> 03:07.958
Do you need help with this box?

03:08.958 --> 03:10.083
"Box."

03:10.166 --> 03:12.666
Can I buy you a drink for helping me move?

03:12.750 --> 03:13.958
That'd be awesome!

03:14.041 --> 03:16.666
I usually go to the bar at noon
because that's when <i>Judge Mathis--</i>

03:16.750 --> 03:18.625
-<i>Judge Mathis</i> starts!

03:18.708 --> 03:21.208
I was physically removed
from his courtroom

03:21.291 --> 03:23.000
for harassing Bailiff Doyle!

03:23.083 --> 03:25.916
Been there, done that. Doyle's a zaddy!

03:30.041 --> 03:32.625
This is where real Chicagoans hang out.

03:32.708 --> 03:34.375
Best bar in the city.

03:34.458 --> 03:36.666
And they got a great pizza puff.

03:36.750 --> 03:41.333
Which I can serve without a food license,
thanks to your buddies the Petes!

03:41.416 --> 03:44.416
Yeah, they work at
air-quotes, "City Hall."

03:44.500 --> 03:49.541
Diane's the queen of making friends
with shady faces in low places.

03:49.625 --> 03:51.666
-Pays to know people.
-Amen.

03:51.750 --> 03:55.083
Speaking of which, our building is a trip.

03:55.166 --> 03:59.208
<i>Apartment 3A, you got Mr. Jorgavich.</i>
<i>High school janitor.</i>

03:59.291 --> 04:00.875
Bad gambling problem.

04:00.958 --> 04:03.000
I know, because we have the same bookie.

04:03.083 --> 04:06.041
<i>Then in 3B, there's Fucks Loud Sophie.</i>

04:06.125 --> 04:08.416
Well, "Fucks Loud" Amanda's here now.

04:08.500 --> 04:09.375
-Yes!

04:09.458 --> 04:11.625
I'll have what she's having!

04:12.208 --> 04:15.208
<i>And then you got Wet Hair Lady down in 1B.</i>

04:15.291 --> 04:17.916
I don't know her name,
but she always has wet hair.

04:18.000 --> 04:19.791
There's one in every building.

04:21.916 --> 04:26.541
Diane, I know it's early to say this,
but… I think you're my spirit animal.

04:26.625 --> 04:27.583
Uh…

04:27.666 --> 04:28.625
No doy!

04:28.708 --> 04:33.208
